<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 4:26PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Grady
and southwestern McClain Counties through 500 PM CDT...
At 426 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bradley, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Dibble, Cole, Alex, Bradley, Tabler and Criner.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
